# GoCanvas MCP server configuration.
#
# The server starts with NO credentials. When hosted publicly (e.g. behind a
# Microsoft 365 Copilot custom agent doing OAuth), the caller's incoming
# Authorization header is forwarded to the GoCanvas API and none of the variables
# below are required. For local use, configure one of the auth options below.

# --- Authentication (choose one; listed in priority order below the request header) ---

# 1. OAuth 2.0 client credentials. The server fetches a short-lived bearer token
#    from /oauth/token and refreshes it automatically (and on 401).
# GOCANVAS_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
# GOCANVAS_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
# GOCANVAS_OAUTH_SCOPE=api

# 2. Static bearer token.
# GOCANVAS_API_TOKEN=your_api_token_here

# 3. HTTP Basic auth.
# GOCANVAS_USERNAME=you@example.com
# GOCANVAS_PASSWORD=your_password

# --- Transport (for public hosting / AWS Lambda) ---
# GOCANVAS_TRANSPORT=stdio            # stdio (default) | streamable-http | sse
# GOCANVAS_HOST=127.0.0.1             # bind host for HTTP transports
# GOCANVAS_PORT=8000                  # bind port for HTTP transports

# --- Optional overrides ---
# GOCANVAS_BASE_URL=https://api.gocanvas.com/api/v3
# GOCANVAS_TIMEOUT=30
